h R = 1, the\ncontroller almost always wins (restores the flock to a V-formation). For R = 2,\nthe game outcome critically depends on which two birds are removed. For the\ndisplacement game, our results again demonstrate that an intelligent attacker,\ni.e. one that uses AMPC in this case, significantly outperforms its naive\ncounterpart that randomly executes its attack.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2017 14:45:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-02"}
